=head1 DESCRIPTION

The structure of database cache configuration that is used for mapping
database paths to cache types in clusters.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 B<REQUIRED> CacheType => Str

The type of disk cache. This parameter is used to map the database path
to cache storage. The valid values are:

=over

=item *

CACHE_1000 E<ndash> This type provides at least 1000 MB/s disk access
throughput.

=back



=head2 DataviewName => Str

The name of the dataview to be used for caching historical data on
disk.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> DbPaths => ArrayRef[Str|Undef]

Specifies the portions of database that will be loaded into the cache
for access.



